properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued February 6 at 3:21AM MST until February 8 at 5:00AM MST by NWS Cheyenne WY
properties.description:
...MAJOR SNOW STORM CONTINUES THROUGH SATURDAY MORNING FOR THE
MOUNTAINS...

...SNOW AND BLOWING SNOW RETURNS TO THE INTERSTATE 80 CORRIDOR
BETWEEN RAWLINS AND PINE BLUFFS LATER TODAY THROUGH EARLY SATURDAY
MORNING...

* WHAT...Snow expected. Total snow accumulations of 2 to 5 inches
expected. A narrow band of heavy snow could still produce a
highly localized area of greater than 6 inches.

* WHERE...Eastern Laramie County including the city of Pine
Bluffs.

* WHEN...6 PM MST tonight until 5 AM MST Saturday. The worst
conditions will occur overnight through mid day Friday.

* IMPACTS...Travel will be hazardous due to icy, snow covered
roads and periods of low visibility in falling snow.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

The latest road conditions for the state you are calling from can
be obtained by calling 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 6 PM THIS EVENING TO 5 AM MST SATURDAY
